'''''Star Wars Insider'' 34''' is the thirty-fourth issue of ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'' magazine. It was published in Summer [[1997]]. Issue 34 marked the conclusion of ''Star Wars Insider''{{'s}} original quarterly publication schedule; with [[Star Wars Insider 35|issue 35]], the magazine began publishing bi-monthly.

==Contents==
===Departments===
"The Editor's Desk"
*"[[Rebel Rumblings]]
*"[[Prequel Update]]" &ndash; New ''Star Wars'' Stars! {{C|by [[Dan Madsen]] with [[Rick McCallum]]}}
*"[[Star News]]" &ndash; Prequel Casting Announced! {{C|by [[Jon Bradley Snyder]]}}
*"[[In the Star Wars Universe|In the ''Star Wars'' Universe: Femi Taylor]]" {{C|by [[Scott Chernoff]]}}
*"[[The Wonder Column|The New Wonder Column]]" {{C|by [[Anthony Daniels]]}}
*"[[Scouting the Galaxy]]" &ndash; Greedo Envy! {{C|by [[Stephen J. Sansweet]]}}
*"[[The Horse's Mouth|Straight from the Horse's Mouth]]" &ndash; X-Wing Rogue Squadron {{C|by [[Peet Janes]]}}
*"[[The Jawa Trader|Jawa Trader]]"

===Features===
*"[[Mark Hamill: The Jedi Speaks]]" {{C|by [[Jacquie Kubin]]}}
*:<small>The first time the ''Insider'' has talked with Mark about ''Star Wars'' since the Special Edition! New exclusive interview by Jacquie Kubin.</small>
*"[[Nathan Hamill: My Father the Jedi]]"
*:<small>Nathan Hamill writes about growing up with ''Star Wars''.</small>
*"[[Jon Fass Morton: Dack Attack!]]" {{C|by [[Scott Chernoff]] & [[Jon Bradley Snyder]]}}
*:<small>The search for the missing Rebel pilot is over. Scott Chernoff and Jon Bradley Snyder speak with everyone's favorite snowspeeder gunner.</small>
*"[[Coruscant: The Manhattan of the Star Wars Universe|Coruscant: The Manhattan of the ''Star Wars'' Universe]]" {{C|by [[Athena Yvette Portillo|Athena Portillo]]}}
*:<small>Athena Portillo talks with Doug Chiang, John Knoll and Ralph McQuarrie about creating the Imperial capital.</small>
*"[[A Real-Life Star Wars Hero: Shawn Valdez|A Real-Life ''Star Wars'' Hero: Shawn Valdez]]" {{C|by [[Stephen J. Sansweet]]}}
*:<small>Steve Sansweet looks at how a courageous young boy with cancer became a permanent part of the ''Star Wars'' universe.</small>

